cs.EM, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.ET, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.EM (Embedded Systems) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on power management for embedded controllers. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the incorporation of dynamic voltage scaling into modern microprocessors. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a feedback control based approach to power management. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) could be a possible category as dynamic voltage scaling is a relatively new technique. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is less likely but still possible as the paper aims to achieve good application performance while reducing power consumption.
